P19.label: place of birth

P27.description: the object is a country that recognizes the subject as its citizen

P39.label: position held
P39.description: subject currently or formerly holds the object position or public office

P40.label: child
P40.description: subject has object as child. Do not use for stepchildren—use "relative" (P1038), qualified with "type of kinship" (P1039)

P108.label: employer
P108.description: person or organization for which the subject works or worked

P119.label: place of burial
P119.description: location of grave, resting place, place of ash-scattering, etc. (e.g., town/city or cemetery) for a person or animal. There may be several places: e.g., re-burials, parts of body buried separately.

P101.label: field of work
P101.description: specialization of a person or organization; see P106 for the occupation

P106.label: occupation
P106.description: occupation of a person; see also "field of work" (Property:P101), "position held" (Property:P39)

P140.label: religion or worldview
P140.description: religion of a person, organization or religious building, or associated with this subject

P166.label: award received
P166.description: award or recognition received by a person, organization or creative work

P184.label: doctoral advisor
P184.description: person who supervised the doctorate or PhD thesis of the subject

P551.label: residence
P551.description: the place where the person is or has been, resident

P547.label: commemorates
P547.description: what the place, monument, memorial, or holiday, commemorates

P463.label: member of
P463.description: organization, club or musical group to which the subject belongs. Do not use for membership in ethnic or social groups, nor for holding a political position, such as a member of parliament (use P39 for that)

P485.label: archives at
P485.description: the institution holding the subject's archives

P793.label: significant event
P793.description: significant or notable events associated with the subject

P1412.label: languages spoken, written or signed
P1412.description: language(s) that a person or a people speaks, writes or signs, including the native language(s)

P6886.label: writing language
P6886.description: language in which the writer has written their work

P26.label: spouse
P26.description: the subject has the object as their spouse (husband, wife, partner, etc.). Use "unmarried partner" (P451) for non-married companions

P20.label: place of death
P20.description: most specific known (e.g. city instead of country, or hospital instead of city) death location of a person, animal or fictional character

P361.label: part of
P361.description: object of which the subject is a part (if this subject is already part of object A which is a part of object B, then please only make the subject part of object A), inverse property of "has part" (P527, see also "has parts of the class" (P2670))

P22.label: father
P22.description: male parent of the subject. For stepfather, use "stepparent" (P3448)

P21.label: sex or gender
P21.description: sex or gender identity of human or animal. For human: male, female, non-binary, intersex, transgender female, transgender male, agender. For animal: male organism, female organism. Groups of same gender use subclass of (P279)

P800.label: notable work
P800.description: notable scientific, artistic or literary work, or other work of significance among subject's works

P103.label: native language
P103.description: language or languages a person has learned from early childhood

P509.label: cause of death
P509.description: underlying or immediate cause of death.  Underlying cause (e.g. car accident, stomach cancer) preferred. Use 'manner of death' (P1196) for broadest category, e.g. natural causes, accident, homicide, suicide

P734.label: family name
P734.description: part of full name of person

P735.label: given name
P735.description: first name or another given name of this person; values used with the property should not link disambiguations nor family names

P3373.label: sibling
P3373.description: the subject and the object have at least one common parent (brother, sister, etc. including half-siblings); use "relative" (P1038) for siblings-in-law (brother-in-law, sister-in-law, etc.) and step-siblings (step-brothers, step-sisters, etc.)

P1196.label: manner of death
P1196.description: general circumstances of a person's death; e.g. natural causes, accident, suicide, homicide, etc.  Use 'cause of death' (P509) for the specific physiological mechanism, e.g. heart attack, trauma, pneumonia etc.

P1343.label: described by source
P1343.description: work where this item is described

P5008.label: on focus list of Wikimedia project
P5008.description: property to indicate that an item is of particular interest for a Wikimedia project. This property does not add notability. Items should not be created with this property if they are not notable for Wikidata. See also P6104, P972, P2354.

P6104.label: maintained by WikiProject
P6104.description: WikiProject that maintains this property, item, or linked pages. If the WikiProject is hosted outside of Wikidata, define the scope using the qualifier "of (P642)"

P1411.label: nominated for
P1411.description: award nomination received by a person, organisation or creative work (inspired from "award received" (Property:P166))

P1441.label: present in work
P1441.description: this (fictional or fictionalized) entity, place, or person appears in that work as part of the narration (use P2860 for works citing other works, P361/P1433 for works being part of other works, P1343 for entities described in non-fictional accounts)

P1889.label: different from
P1889.description: item that is different from another item, with which it may be confused

P53.label: family
P53.description: family, including dynasty and nobility houses. Not family name (use P734 for family name).

P131.label: located in the administrative territorial entity
P131.description: the item is located on the territory of the following administrative entity. Use P276 for specifying locations that are non-administrative places and for items about events. Use P1382 if the item falls only partially into the administrative entity.

P276.label: location
P276.description: location of the object, structure or event. In the case of an administrative entity as containing item use P131. For statistical entities use P8138. In the case of a geographic entity use P706. Use P7153 for locations associated with the object

P407.label: language of work or name
P407.description: language associated with this creative work (such as books, shows, songs, broadcasts or websites) or a name (for persons use "native language" (P103) and "languages spoken, written or signed" (P1412))

P512.label: academic degree
P512.description: academic degree that the person holds

P570.label: date of death
P570.description: date on which the subject died

P577.label: publication date
P577.description: date or point in time when a work was first published or released

P580.label: start time
P580.description: time an entity begins to exist or a statement starts being valid

P582.label: end time
P582.description: time an entity ceases to exist or a statement stops being valid

P585.label: point in time
P585.description: date something took place, existed or a statement was true; for providing time use the "refine date" property (P4241)

P805.label: statement is subject of
P805.description: (qualifying) item that describes the relation identified in this statement

P828.label: has cause
P828.description: underlying cause, thing that ultimately resulted in this effect

P1344.label: participant in
P1344.description: event in which a person or organization was/is a participant; inverse of P710 or P1923

P4223.label: Treccani's Enciclopedia Italiana ID
P4223.description: identifier for the Enciclopedia Italiana on Treccani website

P6208.label: award rationale
P6208.description: qualifier to add short citation explaining the official reason for awarding a prize to a winner by the person or organization who gives the award. Do not use this property to annotate or add comments about a person's award. No quote marked needed.

P10565.label: Encyclopedia of China (Third Edition) ID
P10565.description: identifier for an article in the online version of Encyclopedia of China (Third Edition)

P1706.label: together with
P1706.description: qualifier to specify the item that this property is shared with

P2579.label: studied by
P2579.description: subject is studied by this science or domain

P3831.label: object has role
P3831.description: (qualifier) role or generic identity of the value of a statement ("object") in the context of that statement; for the role of the item the statement is on ("subject"), use P2868

P17.label: country
P17.description: sovereign state that this item is in (not to be used for human beings)

P18.label: image
P18.description: image of relevant illustration of the subject; if available, also use more specific properties (sample: coat of arms image, locator map, flag image, signature image, logo image, collage image)

P31.label: instance of
P31.description: that class of which this subject is a particular example and member; different from P279 (subclass of); for example: K2 is an instance of mountain; volcano is a subclass of mountain (and an instance of volcanic landform)

P569.label: date of birth
P569.description: date on which the subject was born

P2842.label: place of marriage
P2842.description: location where the marriage was celebrated. Use as qualifier for property "spouse" (P26)

P10017.label: Treccani's Dizionario delle Scienze Fisiche ID
P10017.description: identifier for an item in the Dizionario delle Scienze Fisiche on the Institute of the Italian Encyclopaedia website

P10780.label: Radio France person ID
P10780.description: alphabetical identifier for a person on the Radio France website

P898.label: IPA transcription
P898.description: transcription in the International Phonetic Alphabet

P989.label: spoken text audio
P989.description: audio file for the spoken work or Wikipedia article, including audio descriptions

P1534.label: end cause
P1534.description: qualifier to use together with the end date qualifier (P582) to specify the cause

P2241.label: reason for deprecated rank
P2241.description: qualifier to indicate why a particular statement should have deprecated rank

P4220.label: order of battle
P4220.description: arrangement of units and hierarchical organization of the armed forces involved in the specified military action

P7452.label: reason for preferred rank
P7452.description: qualifier to allow the reason to be indicated why a particular statement should be considered preferred

P527.description: part of this subject; inverse property of "part of" (P361). See also "has parts of the class" (P2670).

P710.label: participant
P710.description: person, group of people or organization (object) that actively takes/took part in an event or process (subject).  Preferably qualify with "object has role" (P3831). Use P1923 for participants that are teams.

P50.label: author
P50.description: main creator(s) of a written work (use on works, not humans); use P2093 (author name string) when Wikidata item is unknown or does not exist

P138.label: named after
P138.description: entity or event that inspired the subject's name, or namesake (in at least one language). Qualifier "applies to name" (P5168) can be used to indicate which one

P241.label: military branch
P241.description: branch to which this military unit, award, office, or person belongs, e.g. Royal Navy

P301.label: category's main topic
P301.description: primary topic of the subject Wikimedia category

P921.label: main subject
P921.description: primary topic of a work (see also P180: depicts)

P1038.label: relative
P1038.description: family member (qualify with "type of kinship", P1039; for direct family member please use specific property)

P1290.label: godparent
P1290.description: person who is the godparent of a given person

P1365.label: replaces
P1365.description: person, state or item replaced. Use "structure replaces" (P1398) for structures. Use "follows" (P155) if the previous item was not replaced or predecessor and successor are identical

P1416.label: affiliation
P1416.description: organization that a person or organization is affiliated with (not necessarily member of or employed by)

P4791.label: commanded by
P4791.description: commander of a military unit/army/security service, operation, etc.

P410.label: military rank
P410.description: military rank achieved by a person (should usually have a "start time" qualifier), or military rank associated with a position

P451.label: unmarried partner
P451.description: someone with whom the person is in a relationship without being married. Use "spouse" (P26) for married couples

P598.label: commander of (DEPRECATED)
P598.description: for persons who are notable as commanding officers, the units they commanded

P607.label: conflict
P607.description: battles, wars or other military engagements in which the person or item participated

P6379.label: has works in the collection
P6379.description: collection that has works of this person or organisation (use archives at [P485] for archives)

P7763.label: copyright status as a creator
P7763.description: states if the body of work published during the lifetime of this creator is still copyrighted or in the public domain

P945.label: allegiance
P945.description: country (or other power) that the person or group serves

P2632.label: place of detention
P2632.description: place where this person is or was detained

P3342.label: significant person
P3342.description: person linked to the item in any possible way

P25.label: mother
P25.description: female parent of the subject. For stepmother, use "stepparent" (P3448)

P1347.label: military casualty classification
P1347.description: allowed values:  killed in action (Q210392), missing in action (Q2344557), died of wounds (Q16861372), prisoner of war (Q179637), killed in flight accident (Q16861407), others used in military casualty classification

P1399.label: convicted of
P1399.description: crime a person was convicted of

P1449.label: nickname
P1449.description: informal name (for a pseudonym use P742)

P2031.label: work period (start)
P2031.description: start of period during which a person or group flourished (fl. = "floruit") in their professional activity

P6262.label: Fandom article ID
P6262.description: identifier of an article on Fandom (Wikia). Format: subdomain:Page_title (language-code.subdomain:Page_title for non-English wikis)

P6404.label: Treccani's Dizionario di Storia ID
P6404.description: identifier for Dizionario di Storia ("Dictionary of History") by Treccani

P8852.label: facial hair
P8852.description: style of cutting, arranging, or combing the hair on the subject's face (usually on the chin, cheeks, and upper lip region); beard

P1039.label: kinship to subject
P1039.description: qualifier of "relative" (P1038) to indicate less usual family relationships (ancestor, son-in-law, adoptions, etc). Indicate how the qualificator item is related to the main item.

P102.label: member of political party
P102.description: the political party of which a person is or has been a member or otherwise affiliated

P571.label: inception
P571.description: time when an entity begins to exist; for date of official opening use P1619

P155.label: follows
P155.description: immediately prior item in a series of which the subject is a part, preferably use as qualifier of P179 [if the subject has replaced the preceding item, e.g. political offices, use "replaces" (P1365)]

P576.label: dissolved, abolished or demolished date
P576.description: point in time at which the subject (organisation, building) ceased to exist;  see "date of official closure" (P3999) for closing a facility, "service retirement" (P730) for retiring equipment,  "discontinued date" (P2669) for stopping a product

P11196.label: Baidu Tieba name
P11196.description: name of a specific topic driven forum in Baidu Tieba

P1001.label: applies to jurisdiction
P1001.description: the item (institution, law, public office, public register...) or statement belongs to or has power over or applies to the value (a territorial jurisdiction: a country, state, municipality, ...)

P1317.label: floruit
P1317.description: date when the person was known to be active or alive, when birth or death not documented

P1366.label: replaced by
P1366.description: other person or item which continues the item by replacing it in its role. Use P156 ("followed by") if the item is not replaced nor identical, but adds to the series (e.g. books in a series).

P2868.label: subject has role
P2868.description: role/generic identity of the item ("subject"), also in the context of a statement. For the role of the value of the statement ("object"), use P3831 ("object has role"). For acting roles, use P453 ("character role"). For persons, use P39.

P4342.label: Store norske leksikon ID
P4342.description: identifier of an article in the online encyclopedia snl.no

P156.label: followed by
P156.description: immediately following item in a series of which the subject is a part, preferably use as qualifier of P179 [if the subject has been replaced, e.g. political offices, use "replaced by" (P1366)]

P159.label: headquarters location
P159.description: city, where an organization's headquarters is or has been situated. Use P276 qualifier for specific building

P37.label: official language
P37.description: language designated as official by this item

P2441.label: literal translation
P2441.description: direct or word-for-word translation of a name or phrase (qualifier for name, title, inscription, and quotation properties)

P2963.label: Goodreads author ID
P2963.description: identifier of an author on the Goodreads website

P937.label: work location
P937.description: location where persons or organisations were actively participating in employment, business or other work

P973.label: described at URL
P973.description: item is described at the following URL

P1013.label: criterion used
P1013.description: property by which a distinction or classification is made

P2354.label: has list
P2354.description: Wikimedia list related to this subject

P642.label: of
P642.description: (This property is being deprecated, see details at WD:P642) qualifier stating that a statement applies within the scope of a particular item

P1066.label: student of
P1066.description: person who has taught this person

P1477.label: birth name
P1477.description: full name of a person at birth, if different from their current, generally used name

P1559.label: name in native language
P1559.description: name of a person in their native language

P282.label: writing system
P282.description: alphabet, character set or other system of writing used by a language, word, or text, supported by a typeface

P172.label: ethnic group
P172.description: subject's ethnicity (consensus is that a VERY high standard of proof is needed for this field to be used. In general this means 1) the subject claims it themselves, or 2) it is widely agreed on by scholars, or 3) is fictional and portrayed as such)

P3602.label: candidacy in election
P3602.description: election where the subject is a candidate

P4390.label: mapping relation type
P4390.description: qualifier to more precisely define the relation of the item to the external identifier using SKOS

P5237.label: pronunciation variety
P5237.description: qualifier for IPA transcription (P898), pronunciation audio (P443) or spoken text audio (P989) to indicate the associated spoken language variant

P9775.label: Treccani's Lessico del XXI Secolo ID
P9775.description: identifier for an entry in the Lessico del XXI Secolo on the Institute of the Italian Encyclopaedia website

P2650.label: interested in
P2650.description: item of special or vested interest to this person or organisation

P511.label: honorific prefix
P511.description: word or expression used before a name, in addressing or referring to a person

P737.label: influenced by
P737.description: this person, idea, etc. is informed by that other person, idea, etc., e.g. “Heidegger was influenced by Aristotle”

P802.label: student
P802.description: notable student(s) of the subject individual

P170.label: creator
P170.description: maker of this creative work or other object (where no more specific property exists)

P195.label: collection
P195.description: art, museum, archival, or bibliographic collection the subject is part of

P803.label: professorship
P803.description: professorship position held by this academic person

P1299.label: depicted by
P1299.description: object depicting this subject (object being creative works such as books, films, paintings)

P1424.label: topic's main template
P1424.description: the main template relating to a topic

P768.label: electoral district
P768.description: electoral district this person is representing, or of the office that is being contested. Use as qualifier for "position held" (P39) or "office contested" (P541) or "candidacy in election" (P3602)

P4839.label: Wolfram Language entity code
P4839.description: input form for an entity in Wolfram Language

P5555.label: schematic
P5555.description: illustration of the structure or operation of an object, system, or process

P6394.label: ELNET ID
P6394.description: identifier assigned by the ELNET consortium of Estonian libraries. Format: "a", 7 digits, "x" or another digit.

P7993.label: Treccani's Dizionario di Filosofia ID
P7993.description: identifier for an item in the Dizionario di Filosofia

P9621.label: Treccani's Enciclopedia della Matematica ID
P9621.description: identifier for a topic in Treccani's Enciclopedia della Matematica, an Italian encyclopedia regarding mathematics

spouse.label: spouse
spouse.description: the person they are married to

deathPlace.label: death place
deathPlace.description: The place where the person died.

academicDiscipline.label: academic discipline
academicDiscipline.description: An academic discipline, or field of study, is a branch of knowledge that is taught and researched at the college or university level. Disciplines are defined (in part), and recognized by the academic journals in which research is published, and the learned societies and academic departments or faculties to which their practitioners belong.

place.label: Relates an entity to the populated place in which it is located.

wikiPageWikiLink.label: Link from a Wikipage to another Wikipage

notableWork.label: notable work
notableWork.description: Notable work created by the subject (eg Writer, Artist, Engineer) or about the subject (eg ConcentrationCamp)

influencedBy.label: influenced by
influencedBy.description: The subject was influenced by the object. inverseOf influenced. Subject and object can be Persons or Works (eg ProgrammingLanguage)

award.label: award
award.description: Award won by a Person, Musical or other Work, RaceHorse, Building, etc

firstAscentPerson.label: person that first ascented a mountain
